New Records: Adil Rashid claimed his 200th ODI wicket.
Key Match Events: Mitchell Starc pinned Harry Brook lbw with a brilliant delivery.
Alex Carey scored 74 runs providing crucial late runs for Australia.
Aaron Hardie claimed two wickets in two balls, including a brilliant caught-and-bowled to remove Ben Duckett.
Jamie Smith and Jacob Bethell had a stand of 55 runs.
Josh Hazlewood impressed on his return, contributing to England's early problems.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Australia welcomed back Hazlewood and Starc from illness.
England's new-ball attack showed movement, particularly Olly Stone.
Mitchell Marsh and Marnus Labuschagne took Australia to 145 for 3.
Spin made an impact with Adil Rashid and Jacob Bethell taking crucial wickets.
